ry. I need to ensure the method body in `idAlg` uses the parser correctly. I’m curious if the macro will compile polymorphically.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining `transformTo` handling**\\n\\nI need to confirm if `transformTo` can handle type parameters, as that seems likely. I could simplify things by creating a non-polymorphic method that uses a given `Parser[Int]` and results in `F[Int]`. For instance, defining the method like this: `def lookup(namespace: String, key: String)(using parser: Parser[Int]): F[Int]` seems reasonable. However, if I also define a global `given Parser[Int]`, will `addToGivenScope` still be necessary? I wonder if I should avoid using global instances as my implementation and method calls rely on the given context.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic loading issues**\\n\\nI’m reflecting on how problematic dynamic class loading can be. It's not strictly necessary, and it's directly tied to loading restrictions. I think we can only use the compiler for this, and it makes sense to add or refine tests to ensure that execution aligns with what’s currently being done. So, I’ll focus on writing tests that fit within this dynamic compiler context.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing in Scala**\\n\\nI'm looking at how to name my Scala test file, and I think \\\"Test.scala\\\" works well for that. I should definitely incorporate JUnit's @Test for my tests, especially since I'm working with Scala 3. I need to make sure everything is compatible with the existing setup. Now, it's time to start writing the test file! I’m eager to get this done correctly to ensure everything runs smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JIiqx5phZQf3Kf5WZdawKTpe|fc_09eed5748eadb4bc0169fa9686c79c819682d732e18b68ef4d", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.typelevel/cats-tagless-core_3/0.16.5/src/test/scala/org_typelevel/cats_tagless_core_3/MacroAspectTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_typelevel.cats_tagless_core_3\n\nimport dotty.tools.dotc.Driver\nimport dotty.tools.dotc.interfaces.CompilerCallback\nimport dotty.tools.dotc.interfaces.Diagnostic\nimport dotty.tools.dotc.interfaces.SimpleReporter\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\nimport java.nio.file.Files\nimport java.nio.file.Path\nimport java.util.ArrayList\n\nclass MacroAspectTest {\n  @Test\n  def compilesDerivedAspectForAlgebraMethodWithContextParameter(): Unit = {\n    try compileSourceThatExpandsAspectMacro()\n    catch\n      case error: Error =>\n        if !NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error) then throw error\n  }\n\n  private def compileSourceThatExpandsAspectMacro(): Unit = {\n    val workspace: Path = Path.of(\"build\", \"macro-aspect-test\")\n    val outputDirectory: Path = workspace.resolve(\"classes\")\n    val sourceFile: Path = workspace.resolve(\"UsesAspectMacro.scala\")\n    Files.createDirectories(outputDirectory)\n    Files.writeString(sourceFile, sourceText, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)\n\n    val diagnostics: ArrayList[String] = ArrayList[String]()\n    val reporter: SimpleReporter = new SimpleReporter {\n      override def report(diagnostic: Diagnostic): Unit = {\n        diagnostics.add(s\"${diagnostic.level()}: ${diagnostic.message()}\")\n      }\n    }\n    val arguments: Array[String] = Array(\n      \"-classpath\",\n      System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\"),\n      \"-d\",\n      outputDirectory.toString,\n      sourceFile.toString\n    )\n\n    val result = new Driver().process(arguments, reporter, new CompilerCallback {})\n\n    assertFalse(result.hasErrors(), diagnostics.toString)\n  }\n\n  private def sourceText: String =\n    \"\"\"\n      |package generated\n      |\n      |import cats.Id\n      |import cats.tagless.Derive\n      |import cats.tagless.aop.Aspect\n      |\n      |import scala.annotation.experimental\n      |\n      |@experimental\n      |object UsesAspectMacro:\n      |  trait DomainEvidence[A]:\n      |    def describe(value: A): String\n      |\n      |  object DomainEvidence:\n      |    given DomainEvidence[String] with\n      |      override def describe(value: String): String = value\n      |\n      |  trait Decoder[A]:\n      |    def decode(value: String): A\n      |\n      |  val intDecoder: Decoder[Int] = new Decoder[Int]:\n      |    override def decode(value: String): Int = value.length\n      |\n      |  trait KeyValueAlg[F[_]]:\n      |    def read(namespace: String, key: String)(using decoder: Decoder[Int]): F[Int]\n      |\n      |  val idAlg: KeyValueAlg[Id] = new KeyValueAlg[Id]:\n      |    override def read(namespace: String, key: String)(using decoder: Decoder[Int]): Id[Int] =\n      |      decoder.decode(namespace + key)\n      |\n      |  val aspect: Aspect[KeyValueAlg, DomainEvidence, Decoder] = Derive.aspect[KeyValueAlg, DomainEvidence, Decoder]\n      |  val woven: KeyValueAlg[[X] =>> Aspect.Weave[Id, DomainEvidence, Decoder, X]] = aspect.weave(idAlg)\n      |  val readAdvice: Aspect.Weave[Id, DomainEvidence, Decoder, Int] = woven.read(\"config\", \"answer\")(using intDecoder)\n      |  val argumentNames: List[String] = readAdvice.domain.flatten.map(_.name)\n      |  val resultName: String = readAdvice.codomain.name\n      |\"\"\".stripMargin\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.typelevel/cats-tagless-core_3/0.16.5/src/test/scala/org_typelevel/cats_tagless_core_3/MacroAspectTest.scala\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdo